# GLC CURSOR INJECTION — MASTER BUILD RULES
## Ground Level Contracting | Design System Integration Guide
**Version:** 2026-03-31 | **Authority:** GLC_MASTER_SYSTEM.html (PCL DNA Build)

**Supersedes:** On any conflict with `CLAUDE.md`, older token values, or informal notes elsewhere in the repo, **this file plus `GLC_MASTER_SYSTEM.html` win.**

---

## HOW TO USE THIS FILE IN CURSOR

Drop this file into your project root as `.cursorrules` **and** keep `GLC_MASTER_SYSTEM.html` in the same directory. When prompting Cursor for any page work, prefix with:

> *"Refer to `.cursorrules` and `GLC_MASTER_SYSTEM.html` as the single source of truth. Apply the INHERIT + INJECT rules defined there before writing any code."*

---

## ══════════════════════════════════════════════
## PART 1 — THE TWO LAWS
## ══════════════════════════════════════════════

### LAW 1 — INHERIT (what to keep from the existing build)
When editing any page that already exists in the Cursor build:

1. **Keep all existing routing** — file paths, `<a href>` links, and page relationships stay exactly as they are.
2. **Keep all existing content** — headlines, body copy, phone numbers, addresses, and service descriptions are preserved unless explicitly told to change them.
3. **Keep existing `<section id="">` anchor IDs** — do not rename existing section anchors, as they may be linked from other pages.
4. **Keep any custom images or real photo URLs** — only placeholder/Unsplash images may be replaced or upgraded. Never remove a real project photo.
5. **Keep any existing form logic, API integrations, or contact form handlers** — these are not touched unless the task explicitly calls for it.

### LAW 2 — INJECT (what this document adds on top)
When any existing page is opened for editing, apply the following injections **without destroying what's inherited above**:

1. Replace the entire `:root` CSS variable block with the GLC Master Token System (Part 2 below).
2. Replace the existing `<header>` block with the GLC Mega Nav (Part 3 below) — verbatim.
3. Replace the existing `<footer>` block with the GLC 4-col Dark Footer (Part 3 below) — verbatim.
4. Migrate any existing section's styles to use the GLC token variables (`var(--yellow-core)`, `var(--charcoal)`, etc.) rather than hardcoded values.
5. Add `.gl-reveal` scroll reveal classes to all visible content blocks.
6. Ensure the Master JS block (Part 6) is present at bottom of `<body>`.
7. Apply the correct Layout Pattern (Part 4) to each section based on the PCL→GLC map below.

---

## ══════════════════════════════════════════════
## PART 2 — DESIGN TOKEN SYSTEM (SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH)
## ══════════════════════════════════════════════

The following `:root` block is the **only** place colors, spacing, fonts, and shadows are defined.
**NEVER hardcode a hex value anywhere in the codebase. Always use `var(--token-name)`.**

```css
:root {
  /* ── BRAND COLORS ──────────────────────────────────────────── */
  --yellow-core:     #F2B705;   /* CANONICAL. Never approximate. */
  --gold:            #D9A004;   /* Hover states ONLY */
  --yellow-tint:     rgba(242,183,5,0.08);
  --yellow-tint-md:  rgba(242,183,5,0.14);
  --yellow-tint-lg:  rgba(242,183,5,0.22);
  --yellow-glow:     0 0 0 3px rgba(242,183,5,0.28);

  /* ── NEUTRALS ──────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  --charcoal:#202020;   /* Section backgrounds (dark) */
  --charcoal-deep:   #1E1C1A;   /* Footer, nav, deepest overlays */
  --charcoal-mid:    #3A3632;   /* Borders, rails */
  --white:           #FFFFFF;
  --off-white:       #F2F2F2;   /* Alternating section bg */
  --soft-smoke:      #F2F2F2;   /* Alias for --off-white */

  /* ── TEXT INK ───────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  --text-900:        #0E0D0C;
  --text-700:        #3A3632;
  --text-500:        #6B6560;
  --text-400:        #9C9690;
  --gray-200:        #E0DEDA;
  --gray-100:        #F7F6F4;

  /* ── TYPOGRAPHY ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  --font-display:    'Oswald', sans-serif;
  --font-body:       'Plus Jakarta Sans', sans-serif;
  --font-accent:     'Source Serif 4', serif;  /* italic pull-quotes ONLY */

  /* ── LAYOUT ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  --container-max:   1200px;
  --section-v:       96px;
  --section-v-sm:    64px;
  --gap-grid:        2px;       /* Tile grid gap — intentional tight */

  /* ── BORDER RADIUS ──────────────────────────────────────────── */
  --r: 0; --r-sm: 0; --r-md: 0; --r-lg: 0; --r-xl: 0;
  /* !! ZERO EVERYWHERE. Only exception: border-radius:50% on decorative circles */

  /* ── SHADOWS ────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  --shadow-sm:       0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
  --shadow-card:     0 4px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.12);
  --shadow-elevate:  0 8px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.20);
  --shadow-editorial:0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.10);
  --shadow-heavy:    0 16px 60px rgba(0,0,0,0.30);

  /* ── EASING ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  --ease-expo:       cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);

  /* ── Z-INDEX ────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  --z-header:        900;
  --z-mega:          850;
  --z-backdrop:      800;
  --z-drawer:        910;
  --z-preloader:     999;

  /* ── HEADER HEIGHTS ─────────────────────────────────────────── */
  --header-utility-h: 36px;
  --header-nav-h:     68px;
  --header-total-h:   calc(var(--header-utility-h) + var(--header-nav-h) + 3px);
}
```

