## ══════════════════════════════════════════════
## PART 11 — CURSOR PROMPT TEMPLATES
## (Copy-paste these when starting any page task in Cursor)
## ══════════════════════════════════════════════

### Starting a new page from scratch
```
Using GLC_MASTER_SYSTEM.html as the design reference and .cursorrules as the rule set:
- Build /[page]/index.html following the page sequence defined in Part 6 of .cursorrules
- Copy the NAV block and FOOTER block verbatim from GLC_MASTER_SYSTEM.html
- Use the exact CSS token system from :root (Part 2)
- Apply layout patterns from Part 5 component library
- Follow all 3-plane depth rules (Part 4)
- Add .gl-reveal to all visible content blocks
- Include the Master JS block at bottom of body (Part 7)
- Follow all Hard Rules in Part 8
```

### Migrating an existing page
```
Using GLC_MASTER_SYSTEM.html as the design reference and .cursorrules as the rule set:
- INHERIT: keep all existing content, links, form handlers, and section IDs
- INJECT: replace the :root token block, swap nav/footer with GLC verbatim copies, migrate section styles to GLC tokens, add .gl-reveal classes, apply correct layout pattern from Part 5
- Do NOT change any existing href values, copy text, or form fields
- Follow all Hard Rules in Part 8
```

### Fixing a specific section
```
Using .cursorrules Part 8 Hard Rules:
- The [section name] section on [page] needs to match the [pattern name] pattern from Part 5
- Keep all content intact
- Correct the CSS to use GLC tokens (var(--yellow-core), var(--charcoal), etc.)
- Ensure .gl-reveal is applied with appropriate .gl-delay-N stagger
```

